If you're even  the slightest bit scared of heights you might want to look away now.

A seemingly fearless acrobat performs a record triple flip after leaping from a 180ft crane, the equivalent of 25 stories up, in the latest extreme sport craze - freedropping.

Greg Roe, a Russian born Canadian, performed the incredible stunt in Innsbruck, Austria, landing safely on a giant inflatable airbag.

